        "<p>Over the next few weeks, Alex couldn’t stop thinking about Emma. He saw her in the hallways, always surrounded by friends, her laughter ringing out like a melody. Despite their vastly different worlds, he felt an inexplicable connection to her.</p>",
        "<p>One afternoon, as he was studying in the library, he noticed Emma sitting alone at a nearby table, engrossed in a book. Summoning his courage, he approached her.</p>",
        "<p>“Hi, do you mind if I sit here?” he asked, gesturing to the empty seat across from her.</p>",
        "<p>Emma looked up, surprised, but then smiled. “Sure, go ahead.”</p>",
